### Coaching Staff: Architects of Excellence

The enduring success of the [Stanford Cardinal](/Stanford_Cardinal) men's gymnastics program is inextricably linked to the vision and dedication of its coaching staff.

*   **Thom Glielmi**, the esteemed Head Coach, has been at the helm since **2003**, shaping the program into a national powerhouse. His tenure has been defined by an unparalleled ability to cultivate talent, instill a winning mentality, and consistently guide the team to national championships.

*   Assisting Glielmi in **2024** was Rubén López Martínez, bringing his expertise to the coaching staff. For the **2025** season, the team will benefit from the addition of Carlos Hernandez-Ojeda and Mitchell Soukup as Assistant Coaches, further strengthening the support system for the athletes.

### NCAA Champions: A Pantheon of Talent

The annals of [NCAA Men's Gymnastics Championships](/NCAA_men%27s_gymnastics_championships) are adorned with the names of Stanford gymnasts, a testament to the program's rich history and the caliber of athletes it has produced.

*   **Team Dominance:** The Cardinal has secured an impressive **10 Team National Championships**, with victories in **1992, 1993, 1995, 2009, 2011, 2019, 2021, 2022, 2023, and 2024**.

*   **Individual Brilliance:** Beyond team accolades, Stanford gymnasts have achieved remarkable individual success across all apparatus:
    *   **All-Around:** [Steve Hug](/Steve_Hug) (1972, 1973, 1974), Jon Louis (1986), [Akash Modi](/Akash_Modi) (2015, 2017), [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) (2019, 2021), and [Khoi Young](/Khoi_Young) (2024) have claimed the coveted All-Around title, showcasing their mastery across multiple events.
    *   **Floor Exercise:** Mark Booth (1994), Ian Bachrach (1996), [Eddie Penev](/Eddie_Penev) (2012), [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) (2019), Bryan Perla (2022), Nick Kuebler (2023), and [Asher Hong](/Asher_Hong) (2025) have demonstrated exceptional artistry and power on the floor.
    *   **Pommel Horse:** Ted Marcy (1974, 1975, 1976) and [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) (2022) have conquered the challenging pommel horse.
    *   **Rings:** Marshall Erwin (2002), Alex Schorsch (2007), Dennis Zaremski (2016), [Riley Loos](/Riley_Loos) (2022), and [Asher Hong](/Asher_Hong) (2024, 2025) have displayed immense strength and control on the rings.
    *   **Vault:** Ian Bachrach (1995), [Dan Gill](/Dan_Gill) (2002), [David Sender](/David_Sender) (2006, 2007), [Eddie Penev](/Eddie_Penev) (2010, 2012), Sean Senters (2015), and [Asher Hong](/Asher_Hong) (2023, 2024) have soared to victory on the vault.
    *   **Parallel Bars:** [Steve Hug](/Steve_Hug) (1973, 1974), [Jair Lynch](/Jair_Lynch) (1993), Jamie Ellis (1996), Ryan Lieberman (2010), Brian Knott (2015), [Akash Modi](/Akash_Modi) (2016, 2017), [Curran Phillips](/Curran_Phillips) (2022), and [Asher Hong](/Asher_Hong) (2024) have showcased their precision and strength on the parallel bars.
    *   **Horizontal Bar:** [Jair Lynch](/Jair_Lynch) (1992), Dylan Carney (2006), Alex Buscaglia (2011), [Akash Modi](/Akash_Modi) (2016), [Robert Neff](/Robert_Neff) (2017, 2018), and [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) (2019, 2021, 2022) have demonstrated mastery of the high-flying horizontal bar.

### Athlete Awards: Recognizing Elite Achievement

The recognition bestowed upon Stanford gymnasts extends beyond championship titles, with numerous athletes receiving prestigious individual awards that highlight their exceptional contributions to the sport.

*   **Nissen-Emery Award:** Often referred to as the "Heisman of Gymnastics," this award is presented to the most outstanding senior collegiate gymnast. Stanford recipients include [Steve Hug](/Steve_Hug) (1974), Josh Stein (1995), [Dan Gill](/Dan_Gill) (2004), [Eddie Penev](/Eddie_Penev) (2013), [Akash Modi](/Akash_Modi) (2017), [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) (2022), and [Colt Walker](/Colt_Walker_(gymnast)) (2024).

*   **CGA Gymnast of the Year:** [Taylor Burkhart](/Taylor_Burkhart) received this honor in **2025**.

*   **CGA Rookie of the Year:** This award has recognized emerging talent, with [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) (2019), [Brandon Briones](/Brandon_Briones) (2020), and [Asher Hong](/Asher_Hong) (2023) earning the distinction.

*   **CGA Specialist of the Year:** [Curran Phillips](/Curran_Phillips) was recognized as the top specialist in **2022**.

*   **MPSF Gymnast of the Year:** This conference-level award has been presented multiple times to Stanford athletes, including [Dan Gill](/Dan_Gill) (2004), [Sho Nakamori](/Sho_Nakamori) (2009), Tim Gentry (2011), [Akash Modi](/Akash_Modi) (2014, 2015, 2016, 2017), [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) (2019, 2020, 2021, 2022), [Asher Hong](/Asher_Hong) (2023, 2024), and [Taylor Burkhart](/Taylor_Burkhart) (2025).

### Stanford Gymnasts at the Olympics: Representing on the World Stage

The excellence cultivated within the Stanford program extends to the international arena, with numerous Cardinal gymnasts representing their countries at the Olympic Games.

*   **Olympic Medalists and Participants:**
    *   [Steve Hug](/Steve_Hug) competed for the [United States](/United_States) in **1972** and **1976**.
    *   [Jair Lynch](/Jair_Lynch) earned a bronze medal on parallel bars for the [United States](/United_States) at the **1996** Olympics, also competing in **1992**.
    *   [David Jessen](/David_Jessen) represented the [Czech Republic](/Czech_Republic) in **2016** and **2020**.
    *   [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) was part of the [United States](/United_States) silver medal-winning team in **2020**.
    *   [Asher Hong](/Asher_Hong) and [Brody Malone](/Brody_Malone) were part of the [United States](/United_States) team that secured a silver medal at the **2024** Olympics.

*   **Olympic Alternates:** The depth of talent is further evidenced by the gymnasts who have served as Olympic alternates: Josh Stein (1996), [David Durante](/David_Durante) (2008), [Akash Modi](/Akash_Modi) (2016), [Brandon Briones](/Brandon_Briones) (2020), and [Khoi Young](/Khoi_Young) (2024). These athletes, while not competing, represent the elite level of training and dedication within the program.

